author: Staff Reports sports@seacoastonline.com
title: Seacoast Roundup: Blue Hawks soar to fifth straight win
text: Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 9:44 PM By Staff Reports Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 9:44 PM » Social News EXETER — Senior libero Chelsea deRochemont had 45 digs as the Exeter High School volleyball team won its fifth straight match with a 3-1 win over Salem on Wednesday in a Division I contest. Exeter, which started the season winless after four matches, is now 5-4 on the season. Individual game scores were 25-23, 25-17, 22-25, 25-20. Lex Campbell (eight kills, three aces) and Hanna Schultz (nine kills, three blocks) also starred for the Blue Hawks. VOLLEYBALL Trinity 1 MANCHESTER — The Blue Devils improved to 7-2 with this Division III win. Individual game scores were 25-17, 23-25, 25-14, and 25-17. Senior Ryen Gallagher had eight kills and six digs for Epping, while senior Olivia Goodrich (five aces, 10 kills, 17 digs, 18 assists), and juniors Sophia Randall (seven aces, five kills, 11 digs) and Emily Colban (15 digs) both starred. GIRLS SOCCER Berwick Academy 1 Lexington Christian 1 LEXINGTON, Mass. — Maddie Balas tied the game for Berwick Academy in the 44th minute of this Eastern Independent League contest. Kenza Farid assisted on the goal. Christina Grassie, Tess Varley, Christie Sullivan, Caroline Starr, Kat Reid all played well for Berwick (4-0-2). JV VOLLEYBALL Gilford 2 Portsmouth 1 PORTSMOUTH — Georgia Dickinson led Portsmouth with seven kills, while Mia Saurman had six kills and an ace. Individual game scores were 25-16, 25-18, 11-15. Annah Shaheen (11 assists) and Cassidy Perkins (three aces) also played well for Portsmouth. By Staff Reports
